{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> μάχῐμ-ος</b> [ᾰ], η, ον, <br /> also ος, ον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.185 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: (μάχη):— <b>fit for battle, warlike</b>, ἐπειδὴ μ. εἶ since you're <b>a fighting man</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1368; αἱ μάχιμοι μυριάδες 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] [same place]; τὸ μ. the <b>effective force</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.23, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.4.46; τὸ τῆς πόλεως μ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 830c (but ἀνέωνται ἐς τὸ μ. ={ἐς πόλεμον} 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.165); μ. γένη 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Menexenus” 240a; τὸ μ. γένος [prev. author] “Ti.” 24a, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1268a36 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ μ. (i.e. ἔθνος) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 110c \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; especially in Egypt, οἱ μ. τῶν Αἰγυπτίων the <b>warrior caste</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.141, compare 164 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so later, of <b>native troops</b>, frequently in Papyrus, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 61 (a). 109 (2nd c.BC), etc.: _comparative_ -ώτερος 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 2.22.6 \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: <i>superlative</i> -ώτατος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.102, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 153, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.110; τὰ μ. τῶν ἔργων 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Heroicus” 2.19 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> -μως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Epicteti Dissertationes” 2.9.5. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> = {μαχιμώδης}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" t